# Lower body strength — pairing and placement

When placing **lower-body** strength sessions in combined / tri / multi-sport plans (or extending placement logic), follow these **pairing** rules. Do not surface ambiguous placement to the user as a blocker.

## Same day as lower body — allowed

- Easy bike  
- Easy run  
- Easy swim  

(Only **easy** aerobic sessions — they do not compete for lower-body CNS/structural recovery the same way quality or long work does.)

## Same day as lower body — **never**

- Quality bike (intervals, threshold, sweet spot, tempo, VO2, etc.)  
- Quality run  
- Quality swim  
- Long ride  
- Long run  
- Brick  

## When no obvious day exists

- **Scan the week** for any day that has **only** easy bike, easy run, and/or easy swim (and rest), with **none** of the blocked session types above.  
- **Place lower-body strength there** and **document the choice in code or comments** (e.g. “paired with easy aerobic only”).  
- **Propose a single concrete placement** in implementation. **Do not** add UX or copy that asks the athlete to pick or resolve a conflict; the system must resolve it algorithmically.

## Upper body

- This rule is specific to **lower body / neural / heavy leg** prescriptions. Upper-body strength pairing may follow the existing product rules elsewhere unless contradicted by task scope.
